          "prompt_html": "<h1>MULTIPLE CHOICE 30</h1><p><strong>Questions 31 - 35</strong></p><p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A, B or C</strong>.</p><p>31 In what place are Burmese pythons predicted to be found soon?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    Northern Mexico</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Tennessee</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    India</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>32 Which of the following is one of the reasons why Burmese pythons have established themselves so well in Florida?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    Florida’s laws on the import of exotic animals are less strict than other US states' laws.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Florida has few natural predator that hunt Burmese pythons.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Burmese pythons can thrive easily in Florida’s environment.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>33 On which of the following animal types does the Burmese python <strong>NOT</strong> feed?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    Birds</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Other reptiles</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Small mammals</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>34 Which technique has been used to study the numbers of the animals in the Everglades on which the Burmese pythons feed?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    Surveys of local farmers</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Comparative studies of the numbers of animals killed on roads</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Trapping animals and extrapolating statistics</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>35 Which animal, previously common in the Everglades, has research recently not been able to find there?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    The bobcat</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    The rabbit</td><td></td></tr>